<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../../xslt/element.xslt"?>
<element number="eVitals.27" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="1" isNillable="Yes">
<name>Pain Score</name>
<national>Yes</national>
<state>Yes</state>
<definition>The patient's indication of pain from a scale of 0-10.</definition>
<v2Number>E14_23</v2Number>
<PNNil>Yes</PNNil>
<usage>Required</usage>
<notValue>Yes</notValue>
<pertinentNegative>Yes</pertinentNegative>
<v3Comment>The Pain Score can be obtained from several pain measurement tools or pain scale types (eVitals.28). The pain scale type used should have a numeric value associated with each diagram as appropriate. If the pain scale type utilizes multiple indicators/categories the total should be calculated and entered for the pain score associated with the patient assessment.</v3Comment>
<v3Changes></v3Changes>
<performanceMeasuresGroup>
<performanceMeasure>Pediatric</performanceMeasure>
<performanceMeasure>STEMI</performanceMeasure>
<performanceMeasure>Trauma</performanceMeasure>
</performanceMeasuresGroup>
<restrictions>
	<pertinentNegatives>
		<choice><code>8801023</code><description>Unable to Complete</description>		</choice>
		<choice><code>8801019</code><description>Refused</description>		</choice>
	</pertinentNegatives>
  <constraints>
    <dataType>integer</dataType>
    <constraint>
        <constraintTitle>minValue</constraintTitle>
      <constraintValue>0</constraintValue>
    </constraint>
    <constraint>
        <constraintTitle>maxValue</constraintTitle>
      <constraintValue>10</constraintValue>
    </constraint>
  </constraints>
	<notValues>
		<choice><code>7701003</code><description>Not Recorded</description>		</choice>
		<choice><code>7701001</code><description>Not Applicable</description>		</choice>
	</notValues>
</restrictions>
</element>